  "prompt": "Which state in Nepal speaks pure Hindi?",
  "response": "In Nepal, the state where pure Hindi is predominantly spoken is Uttarakhand. However, it is important to clarify that Hindi is not an official language of any state in Nepal. Instead, Nepali is the official language, and various regions have their own languages and dialects. Hindi is spoken in some areas, particularly among people who have migrated from India or have cultural ties to Hindi-speaking regions. \n\nIn terms of official recognition, the Terai region of Nepal, which borders India, has a significant population that speaks Hindi along with other languages such as Maithili, Bhojpuri, and Tharu. However, there is no specific region in Nepal that can be described as speaking \"pure Hindi\" in the same way it is used in India.",
